Context: The Academic Upgrading Program (A751) is an online program offered by George Brown College for English-speaking adults to improve reading, writing, math, and science skills. New classes begin every month, and the program runs Monday to Friday between 9:00 a.m. and 4:30 p.m. Interested individuals can contact the department at 416-415-2000 or TTY: 1-877-515-5559, or send an email to ask.george@georgebrown.ca for more information. The program's schedule and application deadlines, as well as college news and upcoming events, can be kept up-to-date by signing up. The contact information is also available on the college's Social Media Hub. Please note that the information contained in the website may be subject to change without notice. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
